The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically with morphological analysis, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of a recurrent encoder-decoder model suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE).
